Anti-loop hardening (§4) — Added explicit hard rules: never re-read the same file twice without a state change, never re-run a failed command without changing something, and a hard cap of 3 attempts before the model must stop and ask. This is the most common failure mode in agentic coding.
Plan Mode approval gate (§2) — Made the stop-and-wait requirement more explicit, with a specific list of accepted approval phrases so the model doesn't proceed on ambiguous signals.
Dependency & security guardrails (§6) — New section requiring the model to justify any new npm package, check for CVEs, and enforce Zod validation on all server-side inputs before use.
Git hygiene (§7) — New section with Conventional Commits format, atomic commits, and branch requirements — keeps the repo clean as the project grows.
Testing standards (§8) — Formalized the test requirement with specific tooling (Vitest, RTL, Playwright) and added the "write a failing test first" rule for bug fixes, which prevents regressions from sneaking back in.
Regression Check format (§5) — Turned the holistic check into a structured checklist the model must fill out, making it harder to hand-wave past regressions.
